last_episode_to_air.overview: A changed Susan returns to the Agency. Luke must use his regained powers to save the team.

name: SurrealEstate
overview: Aided by his own remarkable abilities and an eclectic team of associates, real estate agent Luke Roman specializes in “metaphysically engaged properties,” aka haunted houses. Together they investigate, clear and close the houses nobody else can.
tagline: These properties are to die for.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: The Roman Agency welcomes a new agent, as well as a new client with a connection to Luke's past.

episodes.name: The Harvey
episodes.overview: A little boy's "imaginary friend" interferes with his parents' plans to sell their house and move.

episodes.name: For Sale by Owner
episodes.overview: A lovely lake cabin may be haunted or the owner may be faking; a horror novelist seeks inspiration.

episodes.name: A House Is Not a Home
episodes.overview: The Roman Agency takes on a haunted master-planned subdivision and a troubled house by the sea.

episodes.name: Ft. Ghost Child
episodes.overview: When a rap star rents a client's recording studio, a tragic secret is revealed in the playback.

episodes.name: Roman's Six
episodes.overview: The Roman Agency steps in when the visitors to a competitor's Open House are murdered one by one.

episodes.name: Quarantine
episodes.overview: The team locks down in the office to isolate and destroy a murderous demon that followed them home.

episodes.name: Baba O'Reilly
episodes.overview: As Luke considers quitting paranormal clients, he encounters a house that changes his perspective.

episodes.name: White Wedding
episodes.overview: The team is hired by the mother-of the bride to sell a cursed family lodge.

episodes.name: The House Always Wins
episodes.overview: The Donovan house takes center stage as it has sent Nick to the hospital and trapped August somewhere inside.

episodes.name: Trust the Process
episodes.overview: Luke struggles to handle an engaged property; Susan falls in love with a home with a special power.

episodes.name: Truth in Advertising
episodes.overview: Luke deals with a film crew at a client's property, while Susan investigates a strange seaside B&B.

episodes.name: The Butler Didn't
episodes.overview: When a client is held hostage by a ghost, The Roman Agency must hurry to save him.

episodes.name: I Put a Spell on You
episodes.overview: Luke spars with a homeowner during negotiations as Zooey takes on her first sales call.

episodes.name: Art & Science
episodes.overview: Luke must improvise when a client's home traps her inside; August pays a visit to his past.

episodes.name: Set Your Flag on Fire
episodes.overview: A neighborly conflict draws the agency into a feud; Phil's sister arrives to settle the family will.

episodes.name: Gods & Monsters
episodes.overview: Luke helps a client confront the monster under his childhood bed; a new agent joins the Agency.

episodes.name: Let Sleeping Dogs Lie
episodes.overview: Luke reconnects with his estranged mother. Zooey investigates Susan's disappearance.

episodes.name: Dearly Departed
episodes.overview: The Agency must guide a ghost into the light. Meanwhile, Susan is found.

episodes.name: Letting Go
episodes.overview: A changed Susan returns to the Agency. Luke must use his regained powers to save the team.
